Greenland shark. Has one of the longest lifespans of any vertebrae, estimated to be able to live as long as 500 years, or even more.

I know you said species, but if you want other weird sharks:
>Thresher shark
Uses its tail to stun fish.
>Cookiecutter shark
Small parasite-like sharks that take cookie-shaped holes out of larger animals.
>Basking shark
Filter feeder. One of the largest non-mammals in the sea, beaten only by whale sharks. Has a very big mouth. Not much is known about them beyond that.
>Megamouth shark
Smaller filter feeding shark, except even less is known about them. It’s name is hilariously close to Megamind.
>Frilled shark
Deep sea living fossil with a weird shape.
>Epaulette shark
Can survive for extended periods of time in isolated low tide pools by shutting down certain body functions.
>Goblin shark
Deep sea shark that has an extendable mouth.
>Tiger shark
Will eat anything.
